    Package Included:

    • Pen for Surface
    • Spare Tip
    • AAAA Battery
    • Tip Replacement Tool

    Compatible With:

    Surface Pro X/7/6/5/4/3

    Surface Laptop 1/2/3

    Surface 3 Tablet

    Surface Book 3/2/1

    Surface Go

    Surface Studio/ Sur-face Studio 2

    The tilting function is only available for Surface Pro 7/6/5/4/3, Surface Book 3/2, Surface Go, Surface Studio 1/2.

    • Palm Rejection
    • 1024 Pressure Sensitivity
    • No Need Drive or Bluetooth
    • Auto Sleep After 5 Mins Idle
    • 1.0MM carbon fiber tip
    • Pocket Clip
    Read more

    Not Easy to Lose & Easy to Carry

    The pen is made of metal, it can be attached to surface. (Note: only attach to the surface has magnets in.)

    Integrated metal clip is very portable for easily attaching to pockets.

    Read more

    Natural Free Writing and Painting

    1024-level pressure sense responds to very light strokes, drawing detailed sketches and shadows, as well good performance on doodling, professional drawing, and taking notes.

    Easy to Use

    It can work directly after insert the battery. It will recognize the surface when touching the screen. Pay attention that, the negative pole should toward the cap. It will auto Sleep after 5 mins Idle

    Kimwood pen for sur-face also compatible with these windows devices:

    • HP: Envy 17-aexxx, Envy x360 (15-bp0xx)/(15-bq0xx), Pavilion x360 (11m-ad0xx)/(14m-ba0xx)/(15-br0xx), Spectre x2 (12-c0xx), Spectre x 360 (13-ac0xx)/(13-ae000)/(15-bl0xx)
    • ASUS: Asus Transformer Mini (T102HA), Asus Transformer 3 Pro (T303UA) / (T305CA), Asus Transformer Pro (T304UA), Asus ZenBook Flip S (UX370UA), Vivobook Flip 12 R211NA, Vivobook Flip 14 R211NA
    • DELL: Inspiron 13 7373, Inspiron 15 7573
    • Acer: Acer Spin 5, Acer Nitor 5 Spin

    NOTE:

    1. If the pen is unable to write, please downloaded the Surface Diagnostic Toolkit from the Microsoft website. And ran the diagnostic test.

    2. ALL Laptop system must be updated to windows 10.

    3. Please confirm your devices before place order

        5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Surface Book Replacement Pen
        Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2019
        Verified Purchase
        I somehow lost the pen that came with my Surface Book. I bought an official replacement pen, but I am afraid to take it with me for fear of losing another one. I bought this pen as a much less expensive pen that I could carry in my bag. If I lost it, it would not be devastating. I actually like the way this writes better than the original. Seems more pen-like. My signature looks more like what I would get with pen and paper. It has a nice sturdy feel to it. Like the two buttons that are on it. If you look at the pic, the top is the MS version and the bottom is this product. Look and feel is fairly similar. Like the magnet more on the MS version, but other than that, I am very happy with either. For me, I now always have it with me and I am not so afraid of losing it. I keep the MS version at home and this one in my bag. Very happy with the new pen.
